      <div class="subfield"><strong>$f - Subject heading/thesaurus conventions</strong> <em></em><div class="description">MARC code for the subject heading/thesaurus conventions used when field 008/11
                              (Subject heading system/thesaurus) contains code z (Other). Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/subject.html">Subject Heading and Term Source Codes</a></em>.
         </div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">May contain either the name of the subject heading system/thesaurus or a MARC code
                                 designating it. 
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <em></em><div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> <em></em><div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <p></p>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Codes</strong> - For Canadian organizations, the code is preceded by the letters "Ca".
      </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="font_small">
         <div>
            <em>$e - Description conventions [CHANGED, 2010]</em><br>
               In 2010, subfield was made repeatable.
         </div>
      </div>
